{"TopicId":151829,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Control From Here Problem","CreatedByName":"xiaomin","CreatedById":171117,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-10T17:11:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"xiaomin","CreatedById":171117,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-10T17:11:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBefore launching , how can I choose the control model \u00A0if the model is\u00A0shield by a fairing ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nmodule , not model ,sorry XD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Palaceviking","CreatedById":166883,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-10T17:45:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSet that part as root in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVab\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-10T18:43:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou should also be able to scroll in through the fairing to see modules inside and interact with them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xiaomin","CreatedById":171117,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-11T04:52:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you very much\u00A0\u00A0, it works . I\u0027m just a newbie \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xiaomin","CreatedById":171117,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-11T11:23:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222845875\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478799924\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Palaceviking\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Palaceviking said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSet that part as root in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVab\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,when I set the part \u00A0I want to \u0022control from here\u0022 as new root\u00A0,\u00A0it seems the problem doesn\u0027t be solved. I use a\u00A0upside-down\u00A0re-entry capsule\uFF0Cand on launch pad ,the navigation ball is upside-down\u00A0too, I can choose a positive position\u00A0\u00A0part as controlling\u00A0part\u00A0to correct the navigation ball orientation, but the positive part is covered by the fairing. So I need to scroll in\u00A0 \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:17.1429px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:27.4286px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ethrough the fairing\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E and\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:17.1429px;line-height:27.4286px;\u0022\u003Eoperate it , do you have some other \u00A0tips? thanks \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-11T11:27:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222846762\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478863397\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022171117\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xiaomin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, xiaomin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndo you have some other \u00A0tips? thanks \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E add an additional probe core, right side up. Use THAT as the root and control point.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNothing is keeping you from using multiple probe cores or crew pods. Try to think OUTSIDE the box. Really, it is not that hard.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xiaomin","CreatedById":171117,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-11T13:09:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222846765\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478863633\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258254\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tex_NL\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Tex_NL said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E add an additional probe core, right side up. Use THAT as the root and control point.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNothing is keeping you from using multiple probe cores or crew pods. Try to think OUTSIDE the box. Really, it is not that hard.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, I have thought about\u00A0this method. I thought\u00A0 it may\u00A0be solved without more cores. XD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"monstah","CreatedById":95210,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-11T13:18:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222846823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478869742\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022171117\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xiaomin\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, xiaomin said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, I have thought about\u00A0this method. I thought\u00A0 it may\u00A0be solved without more cores. XD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDocking ports can also be controlled from.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xiaomin","CreatedById":171117,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-11T13:23:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222846830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478870293\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002295210\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022monstah\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, monstah said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDocking ports can also be controlled from.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, I \u00A0choose the docking port as controlling part at last , though it i\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:17.1429px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:27.4286px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Eis covered by the fairing .\u00A0I\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E \u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:17.1429px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:27.4286px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Escroll in\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;font-size:17.1429px;line-height:27.4286px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Ethrough the fairing\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-size:17.1429px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;line-height:27.4286px;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;float:none;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eand\u00A0\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(39,42,52);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;font-size:17.1429px;line-height:27.4286px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);\u0022\u003Eoperate it .\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Palaceviking","CreatedById":166883,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-11T17:46:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr.....if you\u0027re willing to go full kerbal, you could fly to orbit with a reverse navball!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRemember to use retrograde instead of prograde for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E etc, don\u0027t worry I\u0027ve actually done this, \u00A0twas fun!! \u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dangerhamster","CreatedById":146944,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-11T17:59:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimply make friends with part commander.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/150122-12-part-commander-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2806669\u0026amp;embedComment=2806669\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2806669\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes what it says on the tin, no muss no fuss.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xiaomin","CreatedById":171117,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-11-13T10:16:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222847060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022151829\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221478886401\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Palaceviking\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2016/11/12 at 1:46 AM, Palaceviking said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr.....if you\u0027re willing to go full kerbal, you could fly to orbit with a reverse navball!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRemember to use retrograde instead of prograde for \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E etc, don\u0027t worry I\u0027ve actually done this, \u00A0twas fun!! \u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhahah, actually , I did. lauched the rocket\u00A0manually use retrograde\u00A0,\u00A0intersting XD\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}